fter introducing the scale-, base-, and sum-invariance characterizations of the law, the book develops the significant-digit properties of both deterministic and stochastic processes, such as iterations of functions, powers of matrices, differential equations, and products, powers, and mixtures of random variables. Two concluding chapters survey the finitely additive theory and the flourishing applications of Benford's law.Carefully selected diagrams, tables, and close to 150 examples illuminate the main concepts throughout. The text includes many open problems, in addition to dozens of new basic theorems and all the main references. A distinguishing feature is the emphasis on the surprising ubiquity and robustness of the significant-digit law. This text can serve as both a primary reference and a basis for seminars and courses.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 30. Aug 2021) 0aDistribution (Probability theory). 0aProbability measures. 7aMATHEMATICS / Probability & Statistics / General.2bisacsh  aBayesian models.  aBenford distribution.  aBenford distributions.  aBenford functions.  aBenford sequences.  aBenford's law.  aFirst-digit law.  aSignificant-digit law.  abase-invariance property.  acomputations.  acomputer science.  adiagnostics.  adifferential equations.  aexponential growth.  afinitely additive probability.  afraud detection.  afunctions.  ageometric Brownian motion.  alinear processes.  alogarithmic distribution.  amathematical hypotheses.  amathematical theory.  amulti-dimensional models.  anatural phenomena.  aone-dimensional deterministic systems.  aone-dimensional difference.  apedagogical tool.  apolynomial growth.  arandom matrices.  arandom processes.  arandom variables.  ascale-invariance property.  asequences.  asignificand functions.  asigni